35 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
36 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
37 Article – Health – General
38 13–3201.

HOUSE BILL 1117 3
1 (a) In this subtitle the following words have the meanings indicated.
2 (b) “Council” means the Virginia I. Jones Alzheimer’s Disease and Related
3 Dementias Council.
4 13–3206.1.
5 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
6 INDICATED.
7 (2) (I) “ELOPEMENT” MEANS BEHAVIOR IN WHICH AN INDIVIDUAL
8 WITH A COGNITIVE, DEVELOPMENTAL, OR NEUROLOGICAL CONDITION LEAVES OR
9 ATTEMPTS TO LEAVE A SAFE AND SUPERVISED AREA WITHOUT:
10 1. THE ABILITY TO RECOGNIZE OR AVOID RISK; OR
11 2. THE ABILITY TO RETURN SAFELY WITHOUT
12 ASSISTANCE.
13 (II) “ELOPEMENT” INCLUDES WANDERING THAT CREATES A
14 RISK OF HARM, INJURY, OR DEATH.
15 (3) (I) “ELOPEMENT RESPONSE DEVICE” MEANS AN ASSISTIVE
16 TECHNOLOGY DEVICE OR A MEDICAL SAFETY DEVICE THAT IS:
17 1. A WEARABLE, PORTABLE, OR INTEGRATED
18 ELECTRONIC DEVICE OR SYSTEM THAT USES GLOBAL POSITIONING SYSTEM
19 TECHNOLOGY, RADIO FREQUENCY IDENTIFICATION TECHNOLOGY, BLUETOOTH, OR
20 SIMILAR TECHNOLOGY TO SUPPORT THE IDENTIFICATION, MONITORING, OR RAPID
21 LOCATION OF AN INDIVIDUAL AT RISK OF ELOPEMENT DUE TO A COGNITIVE,
22 DEVELOPMENTAL, NEUROLOGICAL, OR MEMORY–RELATED CONDITION; AND
23 2. USED FOR PURPOSES OF PATIENT SAFETY,
24 FUNCTIONAL INDEPENDENCE, AND PARTICIPATION IN HOME OR COMMUNITY
25 SETTINGS.
26 (II) “ELOPEMENT RESPONSE DEVICE” INCLUDES:
27 1. A DEVICE DESCRIBED IN SUBPARAGRAPH (I) OF THIS
28 PARAGRAPH THAT HAS FEATURES THAT ENABLE THE SECURE STORAGE AND
29 TRANSMISSION OF CRITICAL INDIVIDUAL INFORMATION TO CAREGIVERS,
30 EMERGENCY PERSONNEL, OR FIRST RESPONDERS TO FACILITATE TIMELY,
31 INFORMED, AND COORDINATED RESPONSE IN ELOPEMENT EMERGENCY
32 SITUATIONS; AND

4 HOUSE BILL 1117
1 2. ANY ELECTRONIC MONITORING SERVICES
2 NECESSARY FOR A DEVICE DESCRIBED IN SUBPARAGRAPH (I) OF THIS PARAGRAPH
3 TO FUNCTION AS A MEDICAL SAFETY AND ASSISTIVE TOOL.
4 (B) THE COUNCIL MAY RECOMMEND THE USE OF ELOPEMENT RESPONSE
5 DEVICES AS SAFETY TOOLS FOR INDIVIDUALS WHO ARE AT RISK OF ELOPEMENT
6 BECAUSE OF ALZHEIMER’S DISEASE AND RELATED DEMENTIAS.
7 Article – Human Services
8 7–112.1.
