10 INDICATED.
11 (2) (I) “ELOPEMENT” MEANS BEHAVIOR IN WHICH AN INDIVIDUAL
12 WITH A COGNITIVE, DEVELOPMENTAL, OR NEUROLOGICAL CONDITION LEAVES OR
13 ATTEMPTS TO LEAVE A SAFE AND SUPERVISED AREA WITHOUT:
14 1. THE ABILITY TO RECOGNIZE OR AVOID RISK; OR
15 2. THE ABILITY TO RETURN SAFELY WITHOUT
16 ASSISTANCE.
17 (II) “ELOPEMENT” INCLUDES WANDERING THAT CREATES A
18 RISK OF HARM, INJURY, OR DEATH.
